reviewText: This is the Alizée concert DVD which corresponds to the abridged concert album/soundtrackEn Concertand the sight of spectacle, passion and dancing provides a new layer of entertainment and excitement for viewers. This movie gives a wonderful feel of being in the audience at the concert with beautiful and clear HD footage. The collection of music she performs is from the albumsGourmandisesandMes Courants Electriques, although the instrumental arrangements and tempos are given fresh, new twists in this concert.If one knows anything about her music videos or performances on television programming such as "The Top of the Pops" and "Tubes d'un Jour," it is apparent how her years of dancing and ballet training (she has practiced since she was a very young child) have refined her skills as a dancer to near perfection. She certainly dances and performs better than most popular singers, and she is very comfortable performing in front of a large crowd often engaging them, such as during her performance ofMoi Lolita. Here are some highlights of this DVD:"Hey! Amigo!," "Mon Maquis" and "Parle Tout Bas" are given wonderful renditions where her voice and singing talent bring a clear and gentle style to her hit songs."Moi Lolita" Here, she gives a very energetic and involving performance of her signature song from the debut album released in 2000."J'en ai marre!/I'm fed up" is a great song performed here on stage with the backdrop of a giant, feminine shoe just like her album cover. She dances very well and slyly while her backup dancers mimic her. The final song, "Contre Courant," features a combination of tribute to her fans and fellow musicians on stage with powerful singing and playful dancing.One of the best songs is the excellent remix of "J'ai Pas Vingt Ans" played during the end credits, which makes the whole film worth watching. "J'ai Pas Vingt Ans (Benny Benassi Remix)" takes her hit song and gives it a catchy remix filled with funk and subtle dance music beats. It is a very fun song.The extras are interesting clips including a performance of  "Amélie m'a dit," a glimpse of her tour in Japan, television spots for her concert tour and behind-the-scenes footage of the making of her music videos.This is an incredible DVD and certainly worth a purchase. I highly recommend it.

reviewText: This absolutely delightful DVD is found by searching MUSIC at Amazon, not DVD.  It's a companion to the CD of the same name, which I also bought so that I could listen to the music in my car and elsewhere.I cannot describe the supreme happiness this DVD gives me.  It pays to watch it more than once.The disc can be played in any region.  It has high-definition video, and Dolby Digital, DTS 5.1, and stereo audio tracks. DVD extras include new footage of Alizée's concert rehearsals, the making of her video, and her trip to Japan.For more detail you can also look at the entry in Wikipedia, the free online encylopedia.[...]
